g.text: ⁘ Handles the user interface and user interactions.
⁘ Communicates with the backend (Sanity CMS and third-party APIs) to fetch and display data dynamically.
⁘ Serves as the backend for managing data related to products, orders, and customers.
⁘ Stores information about categories, inventory, and user-generated content.
⁘ Payment Gateway API: Processes secure payments.
⁘ Shipment Tracking API: Tracks and provides real-time shipment status.
Frontend sends a request to the Sanity CMS API to fetch product data.
Products are displayed dynamically on the frontend.
User adds items to the cart and proceeds to checkout.
Order details (products, quantities, total amount) are sent to Sanity CMS via an API request.
Payment is processed through the Payment Gateway API.
Confirmation is displayed to the user.
Frontend sends a request to the Shipment Tracking API with the order ID.
Real-time order status (e.g., "In Transit", "Delivered") is fetched and displayed on the user's dashboard.
Description: Fetch all product details from Sanity CMS.
Description: Save a new order to Sanity CMS.
Description: Fetch shipment status via a third-party API.
